"{\"uid\": \"hurriyetdailynews.com-toyota-set-to-end-massive-olympic-sponsorship-deal-193993\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Vehicle manufacturerToyotais set to end its massivesponsorshipdeal with the InternationalOlympicCommittee after this year's Paris Olympics, according to reports in Japan.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 124, \"end\": 138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 164, \"end\": 169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9802490538157255, \"rank\": 0.010082739070173524, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Toyota has a contract through the 2024 Paris Games, which was reported to be valued at $835 million when it was announced in 2015.\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 172, \"end\": 178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"score\": 0.9999906861054941, \"rank\": 9.313963611981096e-06, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It included four Olympics beginning with the Pyeongchang 2018 Winter Games in South Korea and ran through Paris.\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999975392668865, \"rank\": 2.460739160721342e-06, \"text\": \"Pyeongchang 2018\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 381, \"end\": 392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.999994023526266, \"rank\": 5.976467049218719e-06, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999976166691, \"rank\": 2.3833014996925476e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been widely reported to be theIOC's largest sponsorship deal.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Citing \\\"sources close to the matter,\\\" Japanese news agency Kyodo said Toyota was unhappy the way sponsorship money was used by the IOC.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 525, \"end\": 533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.7560454615369211, \"rank\": 0.31978125089077586, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"score\": 0.9999906861054941, \"rank\": 9.313963611981096e-06, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\"}, {\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0528024108068657e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The news agency, quoting the sources, said the money was \\\"not used effectively to support athletes and promote sports.\\\"\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Toyota pulled its Olympic advertising in Japanduring the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games in 2021.\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 744, \"end\": 750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"score\": 0.9999906861054941, \"rank\": 9.313963611981096e-06, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It said it was responding to strong public sentiment in the country against staging the Olympics and the IOC's push to hold them.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0528024108068657e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Toyota is supplying 3,000 fuel-cell vehicles for the Paris Games to show off its green technology.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"score\": 0.9999906861054941, \"rank\": 9.313963611981096e-06, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC generates 91\\u00a0percent\\u00a0of its income from selling broadcast rights (61 percent) and sponsorships (30 percent).\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1074, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0528024108068657e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC had income of $7.6 billion in the last four-year cycle ending with the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1192, \"end\": 1195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0528024108068657e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC's 15 so-called TOP sponsors paid over $2 billion in that period.\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0528024108068657e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to Toyota, the TOP sponsors are: ABInBev, Airbnb, Alibaba, Allianz, Atos, Bridgestone, Coca-Cola, Deloitte, Intel, Omega, Panasonic, P&G, Samsung, and Visa.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"score\": 0.9999906861054941, \"rank\": 9.313963611981096e-06, \"text\": \"Toyota\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota\"}, {\"begin\": 1416, \"end\": 1423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alibaba_Group\", \"score\": 1.